episodes.title: Acting Up
episodes.plot: Blanca encourages the House of Evangelista to follow their dreams. Pray Tell joins an activist group to fight for the rights of HIV-positive people.

episodes.title: Worth It
episodes.plot: Determined to be an example to her children, Blanca launches a business venture with unexpected results. Meanwhile, Ricky's travels have unpredicted consequences for his relationship with Damon, and Elektra shocks the ballroom community with a bold move.

episodes.title: Butterfly/Cocoon
episodes.plot: A fatal mishap with a client leads Elektra to seek out the counsel of Blanca and Candy. Meanwhile, moving from friends to lovers proves to be a challenge for Angel and Lil Papi.

episodes.title: Never Knew Love Like This Before
episodes.plot: The Ballroom community is shaken to its core when a valued member is brutally attacked.

episodes.title: What Would Candy Do?
episodes.plot: Competition gets the best of Damon and Ricky as they audition for a spot on Madonna's Blonde Ambition tour.

episodes.title: Love's in Need of Love Today
episodes.plot: After falling ill while organizing his annual AIDS Cabaret, PrayTell lands in the hospital leading to a series of unexpected visitors.

episodes.title: Blow
episodes.plot: The House of Evangelista plan a large prank to antagonize Frederica. Meanwhile, Angel is introduced to the unsavory side of modeling.

episodes.title: Revelations
episodes.plot: Relationships are irreparably damaged when Damon reveals the secrets others have been hiding.

episodes.title: Life's a Beach
episodes.plot: With Blanca reeling from an unexpected loss, Elektra organizes a girls trip to the shore.

episodes.title: In My Heels
episodes.plot: After a medical set back, Blanca struggles to reassemble the House of Evangelista. Meanwhile, Pray Tell confronts old traumas when an exciting new category is proposed.
